1
00:00:00,209 --> 00:00:01,210
WOMAN:  Where has she been?

2
00:00:01,418 --> 00:00:02,628
GOSSIP GIRL:  And who am I?

3
00:00:02,836 --> 00:00:05,547
That's one secret I'll never tell.

4
00:00:06,215 --> 00:00:08,717
You know you love me. XOXO...

5
00:00:10,385 --> 00:00:11,887
...Gossip Girl.

6
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,475
GOSSIP GIRL:  Winter in New York.

7
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:19,102
A Gossip Girl checklist   to surviving the cold:

8
00:00:19,311 --> 00:00:22,147
Cashmere stole for ice-skating   at Wollman Rink...

9
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:26,360
...Jacques Torres hot chocolate for   window-shopping the holiday displays...

10
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:30,155
...and the perfect date to the   Senior Snowflake Charity Ball.

11
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:32,032
SERENA: B, I have other things to do today.

12
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:35,452
Serena, this is the holiday event for high-school seniors.

13
00:00:35,661 --> 00:00:37,788
The crème de la crème will be there.

14
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:41,124
Pictures dominate society pages through New Year. I need a ringer.

15
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:44,545
SERENA: All of these guys asked you? BLAIR: Of course.

16
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:47,756
You think Angelina Jolie considers a project without an offer?

17
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:50,384
-I'm a pay-or-play dater. -Just out of curiosity...

18
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,928
...who's in the lead to play &quot;Guy With No Future&quot;?

19
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:55,055
You think I'm not looking long-term?

20
00:00:55,264 --> 00:00:57,224
Call it a hunch.

21
00:00:57,975 --> 00:00:59,560
-Keith Nelson. -Are you kidding?

22
00:00:59,768 --> 00:01:02,896
Ever seen him without gum? Oral fixation would drive you insane.

23
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:08,277
-Andy Clark. -Outscored your verbal on the SATs.

24
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:10,362
I like an intelligent man.

25
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:12,698
He can whisper mellifluous nothings in my ear.

26
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:14,616
You think you like intelligent men.

27
00:01:14,825 --> 00:01:18,537
The moment he gave you a history of &quot;mellifluous,&quot; you'd rip out his tongue.

28
00:01:21,957 --> 00:01:24,042
Okay.

29
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:26,128
Hey, Dan. Can I ask you a question?

30
00:01:26,336 --> 00:01:28,547
Hey, I'll call you later.

31
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:30,465
[CHUCK SIGHS]

32
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:32,926
So who's next?

33
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:36,013
SERENA: Dan. Hey. -Hey. What's up?

34
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:38,056
-Look. -Wow.

35
00:01:38,265 --> 00:01:39,725
Letters to a Young Poet,  first edition.

36
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:42,686
And the original Herter Norton translation to boot.

37
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:43,895
All thanks to you.

38
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:46,648
I found it at the rare-book store you told me about.

39
00:01:46,857 --> 00:01:49,985
-I'm giving it to Aaron for Hanukkah. -That's very nice.

40
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:52,529
Means he accepted your invitation to the ball.

41
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:54,823
Unfortunately, he will be unable to attend.

42
00:01:55,032 --> 00:01:58,744
Apparently high-society formals don't go with the whole Brooklyn artist thing.

43
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:01,288
Well, it's an acquired taste, to be sure.

44
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,583
-Um.... You still going? -Absolutely.

45
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:07,002
Something I love about the Snowflake Ball.

46
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:10,339
It reminds me of  Anna Karenina,  only by Anna Wintour.

47
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:13,342
-I'll just be flying solo. -My preferred method of travel.

48
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:15,510
That's good. We can hang out, then.

49
00:02:16,094 --> 00:02:19,765
Dan Humphrey, the scourge of high society, is going to the ball?

50
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,975
I know. I'm still reeling.

51
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:23,977
I just realized...

52
00:02:24,186 --> 00:02:26,480
...that the best memories of my past two years...

53
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:30,400
...have been at those events, so I figured, why fight it?

54
00:02:30,609 --> 00:02:33,612
Well, look who's embracing change.

55
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:39,034
I'm assuming that Aaron'll be okay...

56
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:41,244
...with two dateless friends hanging out.

57
00:02:41,453 --> 00:02:44,790
Yeah. He'd better be. He's friends with his ex Lexi.

58
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:47,084
She's coming to town for the holidays.

59
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:50,169
I'm going to the gallery to see his installation. Wanna come?

60
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:52,839
I just have to stop and change first.

61
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:55,425
[CHUCKLES] Yeah. Yeah, sure.

62
00:02:55,634 --> 00:02:57,636
[LAUGHS]

63
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,353
I got your message. What's the emergency?

64
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:09,815
Do you consider Muddy Waters blues or classic rock?

65
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:12,693
I'm reorganizing my dad's record collection by genre.

66
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:15,779
-Why? -I already bound all of Dan's stories...

67
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:17,531
...and cleaned the loft twice.

68
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:21,118
-Did you put Red Bull in your cereal? -No, I just need to keep busy.

69
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:25,247
Otherwise I'm gonna think about my future. Gonna be a hole through my wall.

70
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:27,124
Stop putting pressure on yourself.

71
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:29,751
You're back home and you're still a great designer.

72
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:33,797
-The future will work itself out. -That's not all I'm thinking about.

73
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:35,215
What?

74
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:37,843
Okay, look, I don't wanna be awkward...

75
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:41,179
...but the thing I can't figure out is what happened with Nate.

76
00:03:42,848 --> 00:03:44,057
Is that totally pathetic?

77
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,227
Sitting around thinking about how some guy blew you off?

78
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:51,898
No, but in my experience it doesn't really help either.

79
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,194
I'd...

80
00:03:57,279 --> 00:03:59,489
...move on.

81
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:02,576
Yeah.

82
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:03,952
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

83
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:10,208
Sorry, I told Rufus I'd be at the gallery all day.

84
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:13,545
-So I'll see you later? -Yeah. I'll be here. Literally.

85
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,380
Probably in the same spot.

86
00:04:15,589 --> 00:04:17,257
[CHUCKLES]

87
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:23,305
-Oh, hello, weird documentary girl. -Bye, sad Blair wannabe.

88
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:26,516
-Penelope. What are you doing here? -Snowflake Ball.

89
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:29,603
I wanna commission a dress. Your fashion show was impressive.

90
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,022
Thanks, but the Snowflake Ball's tomorrow.

91
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,982
-And I kind of hate you, so-- -I know.

92
00:04:34,191 --> 00:04:36,485
But this is about fashion, not friendship, J.

93
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:40,197
Hazel and Is keep biting my style, and I need something custom.

94
00:04:42,491 --> 00:04:44,659
-I'm very expensive. -I hope so.

95
00:04:46,203 --> 00:04:49,664
I think we'd better have a second snowflake machine.

96
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:53,960
I mean, it is called the Snowflake Ball. We can't have drizzle.

97
00:04:54,669 --> 00:04:55,670
-Hey. -Hey.

98
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:58,548
I thought the decorating committee agreed on poinsettias.

99
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:02,344
-They did. I didn't. Casablanca lilies. -Sneaky.

100
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:05,806
Hey, thanks for offering to help out. It's really been fun.

101
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:09,184
When you just happened to mention my background in sound systems...

102
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:12,145
...and lack of volunteer hours at the last PTA meeting...

103
00:05:12,354 --> 00:05:13,730
-...I caught your signal. -Ha-ha.

104
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:17,359
Sorry. I had to get out of the house, and I didn't wanna be here alone.

105
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,071
You and Bart still haven't talked.

106
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,322
No. It's my fault.

107
00:05:22,531 --> 00:05:26,284
Since Thanksgiving I pretty much hung up the marital &quot;do not disturb&quot; sign.

108
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:29,079
You're gonna have to talk to him sooner or later.

109
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:31,122
Isn't that what New Year's resolutions are for?

110
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:36,127
Have you decided if you're going to make it to the dance?

111
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:39,214
Witness the fruit of your labors?

112
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:42,341
-Jury's still out. -All right. If you do, save me a dance.

113
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,264
I'll talk to you later.

114
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,396
We need to talk.

115
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:57,983
Fine.

116
00:05:58,275 --> 00:06:00,861
LEXI: Aw. They're adorable.

117
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:05,073
You know, I feel inspired to shop at the Gap...

118
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:09,452
...or validate my self-image with overpriced cosmetics.

119
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:11,997
You sure this one didn't just come with the frame?

120
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:15,166
Women have been the focal point for artists throughout history.

121
00:06:15,374 --> 00:06:17,919
Exactly. Yeah, way to swing at a 2000-year-old pitch.

122
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:20,755
And with Blondie the Bombshell, no less.

123
00:06:20,964 --> 00:06:23,800
-Serena. Dan. Hey. This is Lexi. -The ex.

124
00:06:24,009 --> 00:06:26,845
I was wondering when I'd finally meet you.

125
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:36,688
I probably should have asked sooner...

126
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,566
...but would you come with me to the Snowflake Ball?

127
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:47,324
Oh, I would love to, but I don't think it's a very good idea right now.

128
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:50,577
You mean you haven't told Jenny about us?

129
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:53,622
I know you guys are close and I'm the last person...

130
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:58,001
...who'd wanna come between friends, but Jenny doesn't care.

131
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:01,087
-She pretty much blew me off. -But what if she didn't?

132
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:04,799
I mean, what if you found out that she still liked you?

133
00:07:05,008 --> 00:07:08,970
I mean, Vanessa, I'm really happy right now.

134
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:12,891
Let's just go with this. Please.

135
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,812
NATE: Okay? VANESSA: Okay.

136
00:07:18,146 --> 00:07:21,566
But we're in Gossip Girl country, so rein in your horses.

137
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:24,486
-You're probably right. Okay. -Ha-ha-ha.

138
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:27,364
So tell me, whatever happened between you and Nate?

139
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:29,991
-I'm sorry? -Please.

140
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,703
Your kiss was all over Gossip Girl, and he was living here, wasn't he?

141
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:35,580
Uh, heh....

142
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:36,790
[STAMMERS]

143
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:40,335
Yeah, for a little bit. Why do you care?

144
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:45,048
Now that Archibald is on the rebound, I was thinking of asking Nate to the ball.

145
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:47,884
So, what's the story?

146
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:52,263
Nothing. Nothing even happened between us, so....

147
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,683
I wouldn't beat yourself up about it. I mean...

148
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,518
...it was doomed from the start.

149
00:07:56,726 --> 00:08:00,605
He's Upper East Side and you're, well, here.

150
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:04,943
[CELL PHONES BEEP]

151
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:10,740
You gotta be kidding me.

152
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,327
GOSSIP GIRL:  Sorry, ladies. For those of you hoping...

153
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:16,663
...to find Nate Archibald   under your tree...

154
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,165
...looks like he's already picked up   his mistletoe mate.

155
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:25,130
I don't appreciate your showing up unannounced at a school function.

156
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:28,675
I'm sorry, but you haven't left me many options. We do need to talk.

157
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:30,802
Fine. Talk.

158
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:39,060
It's been a long time since I've been a husband, Lily.

159
00:08:39,269 --> 00:08:41,771
I just want you to know that I fired Andrew Tyler...

160
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,107
...that investigator who gathered those files.

161
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:47,193
No more snooping, no more trying to control you and the kids.

162
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:51,031
It's done and I'm sorry for everything.

163
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:56,619
Thank you, but I don't think that that's enough.

164
00:08:56,828 --> 00:08:59,581
Well, then tell me what is, and I'll do it.

165
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:06,963
I can change, Lily. You know I can. If you'll let me.

166
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,469
I should be back from my trip in time to go to the ball.

167
00:09:13,136 --> 00:09:16,598
If you think about what I've said and are willing to give me a chance...

168
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:19,768
...I'd be honored to accompany you.

169
00:09:23,188 --> 00:09:27,317
I have to go. There's a few more things I have to do inside.

170
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:36,659
I know Lexi can be a bit much.

171
00:09:36,868 --> 00:09:41,247
Ugh. Blair Waldorf is my best friend. I can handle &quot;much.&quot; That felt personal.

172
00:09:41,456 --> 00:09:44,000
She doesn't mean anything. Thinks she's protecting me.

173
00:09:44,209 --> 00:09:47,128
Oh, great. Well, how long is the enforcer gonna be with us?

174
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,672
She's staying with her folks through the holidays.

175
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:52,926
So is that Christmas Eve, or are we talking New Year's Eve?

176
00:09:53,134 --> 00:09:54,761
Or maybe Boxing Day?

177
00:09:55,637 --> 00:09:58,765
-You have any kopi luwak back there? -Kopi what-wak?

178
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:03,228
It's a coffee made from berries that have been passed by the Asian palm civet.

179
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:07,690
It's a cat. I had it in Indonesia. It's delicious.

180
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:10,360
Our cat lives in Florida. My sister has allergies.

181
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:11,778
-That's a shame. -Yeah.

182
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:15,949
We do, however, have this bag here of nondescript beans...

183
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,784
...whose berries have been passed...

184
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,786
...through a corporate infrastructure.

185
00:10:19,994 --> 00:10:21,371
You're funny. Heh.

186
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:23,790
[CHUCKLES]

187
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:28,378
Come on. It would mean a lot to me if you gave her a chance. Please?

188
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:30,213
[SIGHS]

189
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:36,094
Okay, fine. But as long as we're swapping favors here...

190
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:39,806
...it would make me feel much better about you spending time with her...

191
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:43,184
...if you, I don't know, escorted me to my senior winter dance?

192
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:46,729
Fine. Got yourself a deal.

193
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:49,482
So. New plan for tonight.

194
00:10:49,691 --> 00:10:52,819
Dan here has agreed to give me a walking tour of Brooklyn...

195
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,613
...and it might be fun for the four of us to hang out.

196
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:56,990
Get to know each other.

197
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:02,453
I mean, unless the two of you guys wanna hang out alone.

198
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:05,498
[SIGHS]

199
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:10,128
No, no. Sounds great, Lexi.

200
00:11:12,714 --> 00:11:13,882
VANESSA: Anyone home?

201
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:18,720
I have a gift certificate to Grimaldi's and I'm thinking double pepperoni.

202
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:23,016
Everything okay?

203
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,394
How could you?

204
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:28,771
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

205
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:32,775
Really, Vanessa? Lying and seeing Nate behind my back?

206
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:36,905
I'm so sorry.

207
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:39,574
I've been meaning to tell you. Just wasn't sure how.

208
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:43,578
You knew why Nate wasn't calling and it was because he was with you.

209
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:45,830
I understand that you're upset...

210
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:48,875
...but if I remember correctly, you kissed Nate first.

211
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:52,337
I felt so horrible about it that I ran after you and you were gone.

212
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,881
What happened to not letting a guy get between us?

213
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:57,091
-Are you that desperate? -You that jealous?

214
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,302
-Oh, my God. -Sorry you found out this way.

215
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:01,179
I am. But since you have...

216
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:05,433
...Nate asked me to the ball and I think I'm gonna go.

217
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,565
[PIANO PLAYING]

218
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:18,071
What do you want, Bass?

219
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:22,408
It occurred to me while I was having my shiatsu that I should choose your date.

220
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:25,078
-You. Why? -Why not?

221
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:28,081
And it'll let me prove I know you better than anyone else.

222
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:31,417
-Fine. Then I choose yours. -I bring a date for you.

223
00:12:31,626 --> 00:12:35,630
You bring one for me. See who was paying attention to the other's desires.

224
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:40,218
There has to be something to keep you honest and make things interesting.

225
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:43,596
Name the stakes.

226
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:47,766
If you actually like your date, I get your limo.

227
00:12:47,976 --> 00:12:50,353
-For a month. -Fine.

228
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:53,231
And if you like yours, I get Dorota.

229
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,774
-What? Dorota? -Yes, Miss Blair?

230
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:00,571
Fine.

231
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:04,534
By the way, I take my breakfast in bed.

232
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:11,874
What are you staring at? Go polish something.

233
00:13:14,711 --> 00:13:16,546
DAN: I write on these benches all the time.

234
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:19,674
Actually, Norman Mailer used to live in that townhouse there.

235
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:23,636
You can't imagine how many times I thought about knocking on his door.

236
00:13:23,845 --> 00:13:27,348
-Why didn't you? -Common courtesy?

237
00:13:27,557 --> 00:13:31,352
-Okay. It's a door, but whatever. -No. She's right.

238
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:34,981
I don't know why I'm always worried about what people might think of me.

239
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,815
It certainly hasn't paid off.

240
00:13:37,025 --> 00:13:40,570
Wow. Here I thought the Y-chromosome was incapable of change.

241
00:13:40,778 --> 00:13:42,530
Look at you two branching out.

242
00:13:42,739 --> 00:13:46,034
Aaron decided he would escort me to the Snowflake Ball tomorrow.

243
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,243
Sorry. Pause?

244
00:13:47,452 --> 00:13:48,953
-Snowflake Ball? -Yeah.

245
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:52,540
It's this school charity dance that Serena and I have.

246
00:13:52,749 --> 00:13:54,584
And you're going as well?

247
00:13:54,792 --> 00:13:56,294
-Yeah. LEXI: And what?

248
00:13:56,502 --> 00:14:00,131
I'm here to test the Mailer anecdote for your actual date tomorrow night?

249
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:04,052
-At the ball? -No. I don't have a date, actually.

250
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:07,972
Oh, oh. Oh. Ha-ha. Uh....

251
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:10,641
You know what? I just had the craziest idea.

252
00:14:10,849 --> 00:14:12,685
Why don't the four of us go together?

253
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:15,188
-That is if you would be my date. LEXI: That depends.

254
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:19,108
-That little speech you just gave? -He doesn't live there anymore.

255
00:14:19,317 --> 00:14:21,944
-Not really the point, is it? -The man's dead.

256
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:23,946
LEXI: Come now. Ring doorbell.

257
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:26,240
You okay with her coming tomorrow?

258
00:14:26,449 --> 00:14:31,120
Yeah. It's a little  When Harry Met Crazy,  but as long as Dan's fine with it.

259
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:34,624
I'm guessing Dan will end up being more than fine with it.

260
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,250
Meaning?

261
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:39,629
Lexi likes to sleep with guys on the first date.

262
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:44,008
She claims it's a political statement against male-dominated sexual hypocrisy.

263
00:14:44,217 --> 00:14:45,885
Or something.

264
00:14:46,094 --> 00:14:47,845
Can't she just vote?

265
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:50,598
In her defense, she dates very few guys...

266
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:53,810
...but once there's one in her sights, that's pretty much it.

267
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:55,061
[LAUGHS]

268
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:57,397
-You still okay? -Yeah.

269
00:14:57,605 --> 00:14:59,774
-Whatever. -Yeah, whatever.

270
00:15:03,361 --> 00:15:05,488
-Taking off? -Morning meeting in Miami.

271
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:07,865
-I should be back tomorrow. -Sure that's wise?

272
00:15:08,074 --> 00:15:10,410
The marriage thermostat is headed south of late.

273
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:14,414
And whose fault is that? Thanksgiving was a disaster because of those files.

274
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:17,542
You think I don't know who had the combination to that safe?

275
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,003
[SIGHS]

276
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:25,091
Every time I think we're making progress, you show your true colors.

277
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:31,222
Hey. Your housekeeper let me in.

278
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:34,142
-Good, then she can let you out. -What?

279
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:38,938
And tell your friend Vanessa it's not wise to fish in our pond.

280
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,357
Well, she's not my friend.

281
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:42,733
Really?

282
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:46,028
Because we were just trying to think of a way to send her a little message.

283
00:15:46,237 --> 00:15:47,613
[DOOR OPENS]

284
00:15:48,448 --> 00:15:50,700
Feast your eyes, ladies.

285
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:52,660
ISABEL: Well? What do you think?

286
00:15:53,244 --> 00:15:56,622
I think you shouldn't stand in front of a light in that dress.

287
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:58,666
[LAUGHS]

288
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:03,629
ISABEL: Oh, my God. It's see-through. -One way to be the center of attention.

289
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:05,756
At least you don't have to worry about going home alone.

290
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:07,508
[GIRLS LAUGH]

291
00:16:07,717 --> 00:16:10,386
-What do you think Vanessa's wearing? -She's going?

292
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:12,180
Yeah. With Nate.

293
00:16:17,185 --> 00:16:20,646
Jenny, Isabel's dress looks a little like one of yours, don't you think?

294
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:24,025
No, not at all. I know of a little something called lining.

295
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,570
Well, what if you didn't?

296
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:33,576
Snowflake or Snowfake?   Either way, it's gonna be a ball.

297
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:37,580
BLAIR: Chuck is in for the shock of his life.

298
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,582
I have depths he'll never plumb...

299
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:42,043
...but I know every inch of his wafer-thin soul.

300
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,794
What do you think?

301
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:47,673
You're right. Louboutin peep-toes. Always.

302
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:50,134
Just so you know, seeing someone with your ex...

303
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:51,928
...even if you're ready, not easy.

304
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:56,015
I assume you're talking about your lame outer-boroughs double date last night.

305
00:16:56,224 --> 00:16:58,100
-What happened? -Nothing. It was great.

306
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:01,646
Right up until Dan asked Lexi to go with him to the Snowflake Ball.

307
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:03,439
So they're going to the dance?

308
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:06,901
And I found out she tends to extend herself to guys on a first date.

309
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:09,111
-So? -So? We're friends.

310
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:11,447
Shouldn't I give him a heads up or something?

311
00:17:11,656 --> 00:17:15,201
Absolutely. Guys hate to be caught off-guard with sex on the first date.

312
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:18,287
You're right. You're right. I should just not think about it.

313
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:20,957
Exactly. Like I'm sure Dan doesn't think about you...

314
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:23,042
...and Aaron all horizontal and sweaty.

315
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:28,839
Wait, you have slept together, haven't you?

316
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:31,759
Why not?

317
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:35,012
He's hot. You like him. How often you find that in the same guy?

318
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:37,265
Which is why I haven't rushed into anything.

319
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:39,517
You wanna wait, fine, but in the meantime...

320
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:43,479
...Dan is going to be taking a ride on the Lexicoaster. Think about it.

321
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:48,109
VANESSA: Jenny.

322
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:50,570
-What are you doing here? -I'm still mad at you.

323
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:53,281
You're gonna kill me and put me in the garment bag?

324
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:54,865
I couldn't sleep last night.

325
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:58,494
I was up half the night making this before I realized who it was for.

326
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:01,747
-You made that for me? -Yeah.

327
00:18:01,956 --> 00:18:05,751
I mean, I said some pretty awful things because I was hurt.

328
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:09,880
So I guess just consider this a peace offering. You'll look great.

329
00:18:10,298 --> 00:18:12,091
[CHUCKLES]

330
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:16,637
-I don't know what to say. -Just say you'll try it on.

331
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:19,849
Okay.

332
00:18:24,145 --> 00:18:27,648
I thought I made it clear that we need to find Chuck the perfect date.

333
00:18:27,857 --> 00:18:30,735
Kristin Curran is the loosest girl in our class.

334
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,529
Don't you know Chuck doesn't like his fruit pre-picked?

335
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:35,698
She has long hair. In Poland, long hair--

336
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:39,619
And Elizabeth Phillips is somewhere between Mormon and moron.

337
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:42,455
-How'd you come up with these? -Facebook. Joined groups.

338
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:44,665
This has to be Chuck's dream girl.

339
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:48,586
Intelligent but not a bookworm, strong-willed but still feminine.

340
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:49,795
An equal.

341
00:18:50,004 --> 00:18:52,465
And he likes brunettes with deep brown eyes.

342
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:54,383
-But Miss Blair, that's you-- -No.

343
00:18:54,592 --> 00:18:57,845
That girl is out there and you better hope for your sake I find her.

344
00:18:58,054 --> 00:19:00,806
Please. I don't want to shine Mr. Chuck's shoes for month.

345
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:02,391
His shoes if you're lucky.

346
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,852
-What? -Nothing. Now get back to work.

347
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:06,270
Tick-tock. Tick-tock.

348
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:08,147
[LINE RINGING]

349
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:10,441
SERENA:  Hello?  -You know, rent a tux in Brooklyn...

350
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:12,360
...they throw in the shoes?

351
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:15,112
No, I didn't know that.

352
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:16,656
What's going on?

353
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:20,660
Well, this is stupid, but I wanted to make sure this was all okay with you.

354
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,371
You know, you, me, Lexi, Aaron.

355
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,248
Of course. Why wouldn't it be?

356
00:19:26,457 --> 00:19:28,292
I don't know. Dramatic precedent?

357
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:30,252
Well, I think we've outgrown that.

358
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,797
Good. Good. Me too.

359
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:36,050
I have to say, I'm really looking forward to this tonight.

360
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:38,969
Okay, great.

361
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:43,307
-I'll just talk to you later, then.  -Yeah, I'll see you.

362
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:47,770
Oh....

363
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,356
So?

364
00:19:53,484 --> 00:19:55,778
I so appreciate you coming tonight.

365
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,405
I know. You've thanked me.

366
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,657
I know.

367
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:00,950
I know, but...

368
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:08,666
...I wanna thank you properly.

369
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:14,880
-Later tonight. -Really?

370
00:20:18,092 --> 00:20:19,593
[CHUCKLES]

371
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:25,266
-There. -It's beautiful.

372
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,767
[CHUCKLES]

373
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:29,603
-Jenny, about the whole-- -Handbag.

374
00:20:30,688 --> 00:20:31,981
Here. I'm gonna get going.

375
00:20:33,107 --> 00:20:35,401
Wait. I have to tell you something.

376
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:38,696
When I flipped out yesterday and asked if you were jealous...

377
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,241
...it's because I always have been, of you and Dan.

378
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:44,326
To me, you guys had it all.

379
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:48,998
And it doesn't excuse what I'm about to tell you, but--

380
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:51,292
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

381
00:20:53,127 --> 00:20:54,587
JENNY: Um....

382
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:58,841
It's cool. You don't have to tell me. I don't--

383
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,718
I don't wanna know. It's fine.

384
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,596
Have fun tonight, though, okay? Bye.

385
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:09,435
Hey. I'm glad you called.

386
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:12,354
There's something I have to talk to you about.

387
00:21:12,563 --> 00:21:17,651
No. I'd rather do it tonight, in person, actually.

388
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:19,361
LILY: Hello, Mrs. Landingham.

389
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:24,325
Could you tell Bart that I'm waiting for him to go to the Snowflake Ball?

390
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:29,079
Wha--? A meeting? Well, who's it with?

391
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,375
Andrew Tyler?

392
00:21:34,168 --> 00:21:35,252
Let me call you back.

393
00:21:55,231 --> 00:21:56,941
[DIALING]

394
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:01,195
Hi, it's me.

395
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:08,035
Could you inform Mr. Bass that my plans have changed?

396
00:22:08,244 --> 00:22:13,040
I won't be waiting, and he shouldn't come to the ball.

397
00:22:17,628 --> 00:22:20,756
[&quot;THE SUN AIN'T SHINING NO MORE&quot; PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

398
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:33,769
We all set?

399
00:22:33,978 --> 00:22:36,105
Jenny called after she delivered the dress.

400
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:40,276
-Brooklyn Betty walks in, cue the song. -Hazel's new boyfriend...

401
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:43,028
-...hits her with the spotlight. -I hate you all.

402
00:22:43,237 --> 00:22:46,073
And we expose her in nothing but her cheap glass slippers.

403
00:22:46,282 --> 00:22:48,450
Nate. Save me a dance?

404
00:22:48,659 --> 00:22:51,745
Oh, yeah, sure.

405
00:22:54,415 --> 00:22:55,541
Are you Chuck Bass?

406
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:57,793
Are you Blair's girl? Not bad.

407
00:22:58,002 --> 00:23:00,880
You know, the roof has a spectacular view of the city.

408
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,298
Oh.

409
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:04,550
Excuse me, he's taken, shoo.

410
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:06,384
You look lovely.

411
00:23:07,261 --> 00:23:09,722
Not as lovely as I'll look in my limo.

412
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:12,433
-So where's my Prince Un-Charming? -Sandbox rules.

413
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,351
Show you mine if you show me yours.

414
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:18,772
Fine, here she comes. Justine, this is Chuck Bass.

415
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:21,609
Very nice to meet you.

416
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:30,618
[LAUGHS]

417
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:32,453
You can't be serious.

418
00:23:33,913 --> 00:23:37,291
I need to talk to you. Excuse us.

419
00:23:48,052 --> 00:23:51,931
-Looks like tonight's the night. -What are you talking about?

420
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:55,100
Aaron likes to play things close to the vest.

421
00:23:55,309 --> 00:23:56,477
It took arm-twisting...

422
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:59,939
...but I found out Serena gave him the green light for tonight.

423
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:02,983
Oh. You mean, they haven't had sex?

424
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:06,236
You're not as quick as you pretend to be.

425
00:24:06,612 --> 00:24:08,656
[CHUCKLES]

426
00:24:08,906 --> 00:24:12,117
-Do you care? -I don't. I don't.

427
00:24:14,078 --> 00:24:15,120
Okay.

428
00:24:18,791 --> 00:24:21,085
We both know that I'm your one and only...

429
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:23,461
...and a knockoff seemed like the best option.

430
00:24:23,671 --> 00:24:25,631
My thinking exactly.

431
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:26,840
Fine.

432
00:24:27,049 --> 00:24:28,801
If beta Bass is like the original...

433
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:32,388
...I have no doubt that sooner or later he'll disappoint me.

434
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:34,056
I'm curious if the new Blair...

435
00:24:34,264 --> 00:24:37,393
...has all the features I so enjoyed on the old model.

436
00:24:37,601 --> 00:24:40,688
-So the bet is still on? -Unless you're prepared to concede.

437
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:43,440
To you? Never.

438
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,905
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

439
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:52,032
It was nice to meet you.

440
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:54,034
[DEERHEART'S &quot;BREAKDOWN&quot; PLAYING]

441
00:24:54,243 --> 00:24:55,536
[MOUTHS]  Okay.

442
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:06,338
Hi, Rufus.

443
00:25:06,547 --> 00:25:08,132
Wow.

444
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:11,468
Where's Bart?

445
00:25:12,886 --> 00:25:13,929
I'm leaving him.

446
00:25:15,764 --> 00:25:18,100
I'm doing it for me, I don't expect anything.

447
00:25:20,518 --> 00:25:22,021
Except maybe a dance.

448
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,313
[CHUCKLES]

449
00:26:05,856 --> 00:26:06,940
[GIGGLES]

450
00:26:07,149 --> 00:26:10,152
Uh-- So you seem like you're having a good time.

451
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,362
-So do you guys. -Mm.

452
00:26:13,864 --> 00:26:16,075
-What? -Uh....

453
00:26:16,283 --> 00:26:20,496
Lexi told me about your and Aaron's plans tonight, that's all.

454
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:23,707
Oh. I am gonna miss her when she's gone.

455
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:26,251
I only mention it because we're friends now...

456
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:29,338
...so if there's anything you wanna talk about....

457
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:31,965
Well, what's there to talk about?

458
00:26:32,174 --> 00:26:34,301
We've been dating, gotten to know each other.

459
00:26:34,510 --> 00:26:36,929
-It's not like we're rushing into anything. -Right.

460
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:39,389
And that's important.

461
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:41,225
Well, it is to some people.

462
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:45,687
I know Lexi has a more &quot;come hither&quot; attitude about sex.

463
00:26:45,896 --> 00:26:47,940
Right. Wait. What?

464
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:51,819
Well, she's planning on seducing you tonight.

465
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:54,154
Seducing me?

466
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:58,659
Wow.

467
00:26:59,701 --> 00:27:01,578
What does &quot;wow&quot; mean?

468
00:27:01,787 --> 00:27:08,710
Well, I always assumed that I would, you know, again sooner or later.

469
00:27:08,919 --> 00:27:11,839
&quot;Assumed&quot; is a strong word. &quot;Hoped&quot; is more accurate.

470
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:16,385
What?

471
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:18,720
Mm.

472
00:27:18,929 --> 00:27:20,347
Nothing, I just....

473
00:27:20,556 --> 00:27:22,307
You and Lexi together....

474
00:27:22,516 --> 00:27:25,727
I just thought sex was meaningful to you, that's all.

475
00:27:26,311 --> 00:27:29,106
It is. Especially when I haven't had it in a long time.

476
00:27:33,527 --> 00:27:36,321
Right. Okay, then. Have fun.

477
00:27:37,698 --> 00:27:41,118
Serena. I was kidding.

478
00:27:41,326 --> 00:27:43,245
There you are.

479
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:45,247
I'm parched. Drinks?

480
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,457
Ha-ha. Sure.

481
00:27:47,665 --> 00:27:50,794
[AFTERNOONS' &quot;SATURDAY MORNING (AFTER THE FUNERAL)&quot; PLAYS]

482
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:57,467
VANESSA: Jenny?

483
00:27:57,675 --> 00:28:00,304
-What are you doing here? -Hi.

484
00:28:00,596 --> 00:28:02,556
Uh....

485
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:08,812
It doesn't matter.

486
00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:14,067
I'm ending things with Nate.

487
00:28:14,943 --> 00:28:18,030
-What? -I never meant to hurt you.

488
00:28:18,488 --> 00:28:19,697
Please believe that.

489
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:24,953
Where is she? How long does that subway thing take?

490
00:28:25,162 --> 00:28:27,956
-Maybe she's not coming. -Or Little J had second thoughts.

491
00:28:32,002 --> 00:28:33,879
Vanessa.

492
00:28:34,421 --> 00:28:36,465
Finally. Showtime.

493
00:28:42,262 --> 00:28:44,014
Hey.

494
00:28:45,766 --> 00:28:48,477
-Wow, you look gorgeous. -Thank you.

495
00:28:52,689 --> 00:28:54,608
I need to tell you something...

496
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:56,944
...and I need for you not to say anything.

497
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:00,614
Okay.

498
00:29:03,825 --> 00:29:10,249
I've never felt this way about anyone before. Never.

499
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:16,755
And it made me do something that I can't believe I did.

500
00:29:22,678 --> 00:29:24,513
Jenny never got your letter.

501
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:27,557
That's why you never heard from her again.

502
00:29:28,058 --> 00:29:29,434
I took it before she saw it.

503
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:35,274
And I'm sorry.

504
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:39,653
Vanessa.

505
00:29:41,655 --> 00:29:42,698
[CROWD GASPS, LAUGHTER]

506
00:29:42,906 --> 00:29:44,324
MAN 1: Hey, you see that?

507
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:50,580
MAN 2: No way. WOMAN 1: You see that? Look at that.

508
00:29:56,753 --> 00:29:58,797
WOMAN 2: Nice dress.

509
00:30:01,883 --> 00:30:03,719
WOMAN 3: You can see everything.

510
00:30:05,262 --> 00:30:06,888
[LAUGHTER CONTINUES]

511
00:30:09,266 --> 00:30:10,309
GOSSIP GIRL:  Poor Vanessa.

512
00:30:10,517 --> 00:30:14,146
Even Cinderella was given the courtesy   of a stealth getaway.

513
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:17,232
Then again,   what's a trio of ugly stepsisters...

514
00:30:17,441 --> 00:30:19,484
...compared to Jenny Humphrey?

515
00:30:19,693 --> 00:30:21,445
Vanessa, here. Take this.

516
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:24,489
Vanessa, wait. Please.

517
00:30:24,698 --> 00:30:29,578
Looks like it might turn out to be   an unhappily ever after for everyone.

518
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,834
Jenny. Did you do that to Vanessa?

519
00:30:39,588 --> 00:30:41,423
Yeah.

520
00:30:42,591 --> 00:30:45,552
-You don't understand. She completely-- -She what? She lied?

521
00:30:45,761 --> 00:30:47,971
She went behind your back?

522
00:30:48,180 --> 00:30:50,432
So what?

523
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:54,436
For that she deserved to be publicly humiliated?

524
00:30:55,103 --> 00:30:56,313
She's your friend, Jenny.

525
00:31:01,902 --> 00:31:05,280
You know, there's no reason for me to tell you this now...

526
00:31:05,489 --> 00:31:10,827
...but I wrote you after the fashion show, telling you I had feelings for you.

527
00:31:13,455 --> 00:31:14,873
-I never got that. -No, I know.

528
00:31:15,082 --> 00:31:16,208
Vanessa stole it.

529
00:31:17,334 --> 00:31:20,587
But she felt so bad about it, she came and told me the truth.

530
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:29,096
Okay, look, I know what you must think of me right now...

531
00:31:29,304 --> 00:31:32,307
-...but if I had gotten that-- -I'm glad you didn't.

532
00:31:32,516 --> 00:31:37,396
Honestly, you're not who I thought you were.

533
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:48,615
-Where are they? -Relax. They'll be here somewhere.

534
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:52,702
This is the worst out-of-body experience ever.

535
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:54,996
Hey. Explain this.

536
00:31:55,205 --> 00:31:59,543
After you and Chuck walked off, Justine and I got to talking.

537
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:02,295
JUSTINE: He took me up to the roof and we looked over the city.

538
00:32:02,504 --> 00:32:04,214
-Of course he did. -We just knew...

539
00:32:04,423 --> 00:32:07,300
-...we were meant for each other. -But she's me. Only less.

540
00:32:07,509 --> 00:32:11,972
-I gave her that headband. -We're as surprised as you are.

541
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:19,688
Everyone, even our doppelgangers, can work it out, but we can't?

542
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:25,110
[SCOFFS]

543
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:31,199
I hate that I have to hurt him.

544
00:32:31,408 --> 00:32:35,203
I know it sounds strange, but I suddenly feel horrible about what I have to do.

545
00:32:35,412 --> 00:32:37,205
I'd be worried about you if you didn't.

546
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:39,166
And the kids.

547
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:42,836
-Eric has become so accustomed to him-- -Eric wants you to be happy.

548
00:32:44,671 --> 00:32:48,633
I never thought my life would turn out like this.

549
00:32:50,719 --> 00:32:52,762
I've always tried to do the right thing.

550
00:32:57,392 --> 00:32:58,435
That's all you can do.

551
00:32:59,936 --> 00:33:04,566
Just smile and fake it.

552
00:33:09,905 --> 00:33:11,198
Tell me something, Rufus.

553
00:33:13,074 --> 00:33:16,620
-What? -Something you shouldn't.

554
00:33:21,082 --> 00:33:23,627
I never wanted to weigh in about your relationship.

555
00:33:24,711 --> 00:33:28,131
I was afraid of what I might say.

556
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,384
Which was?

557
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:42,521
I let you go on your wedding day...

558
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:46,483
...because I was afraid I couldn't give you what you needed.

559
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:49,444
I wasn't sure what I needed.

560
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:53,698
And I have regretted it every day since.

561
00:34:03,792 --> 00:34:05,961
As much as I appreciate company...

562
00:34:06,169 --> 00:34:09,798
...I thought I made myself clear: Your services are no longer required.

563
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:11,841
Trust me. You gave me a final assignment...

564
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:13,718
...and you do wanna know what I found out.

565
00:34:13,927 --> 00:34:15,011
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

566
00:34:15,220 --> 00:34:16,888
This isn't a good time, Chuck.

567
00:34:17,097 --> 00:34:20,058
CHUCK:  She's here.  -What are you talking about?

568
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:23,019
Lily's at the ball with Rufus Humphrey.

569
00:34:23,603 --> 00:34:26,481
And from what I'm seeing, you should get down here now.

570
00:34:34,698 --> 00:34:36,908
What do you have?

571
00:34:46,126 --> 00:34:48,086
LILY: Charles.

572
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:51,381
[LILY SIGHS]

573
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:54,718
You've been good for him. Good for us.

574
00:34:55,885 --> 00:34:58,054
I always liked you, regardless of how I acted.

575
00:35:01,016 --> 00:35:02,058
He's on his way here.

576
00:35:06,813 --> 00:35:09,065
You owe him a conversation.

577
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:17,324
Vanessa. Wait.

578
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:18,950
[SIGHS]

579
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:23,413
You stole my letter.

580
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:26,124
I know.

581
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:29,878
Is there anything else you wanna tell me?

582
00:35:31,921 --> 00:35:33,089
Pretty sure that was it.

583
00:35:37,594 --> 00:35:41,097
You said you never felt this way about anyone before.

584
00:35:42,474 --> 00:35:43,516
Is that true?

585
00:35:45,310 --> 00:35:47,354
[VOICE BREAKING] Does it matter?

586
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:53,193
Listen. After all we've been through...

587
00:35:55,487 --> 00:35:58,615
...when you walked away tonight, all I could think was:

588
00:35:58,823 --> 00:36:00,408
&quot;She's the one I wanna be with.&quot;

589
00:36:06,539 --> 00:36:09,834
So, yeah, it matters.

590
00:36:23,556 --> 00:36:26,226
Yes, it's easy for you to say...

591
00:36:26,434 --> 00:36:29,437
...because you didn't just pull a Janet Jackson at the Snowflake Ball.

592
00:36:29,646 --> 00:36:31,398
[LAUGHS]

593
00:36:32,941 --> 00:36:37,278
-You wanna grab a drink? -Yes, I would.

594
00:36:37,487 --> 00:36:39,239
Somewhere dark with no backlighting.

595
00:36:39,948 --> 00:36:41,408
Well, maybe a little backlighting.

596
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,368
[BOTH LAUGH]

597
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:46,287
-Let's go. -Okay.

598
00:36:47,747 --> 00:36:48,832
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

599
00:36:56,339 --> 00:36:58,133
We saw you try and save her.

600
00:36:58,341 --> 00:37:01,261
-Should have known you didn't have it. -You never did.

601
00:37:02,429 --> 00:37:06,141
I don't know what's more pathetic, that I wanted to be you, or I was scared.

602
00:37:06,349 --> 00:37:09,144
Either way that leaves you with pathetic. You and your friend.

603
00:37:09,352 --> 00:37:13,940
Oh-- Oh, Vanessa's 10 times the person you will ever be.

604
00:37:14,149 --> 00:37:16,443
-That is why you hate her. -Easy to talk big...

605
00:37:16,651 --> 00:37:18,069
...when you're in Brooklyn.

606
00:37:20,864 --> 00:37:22,907
Well, maybe we should change that.

607
00:37:23,116 --> 00:37:24,325
I'll see you guys around.

608
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:27,662
[THE ASTEROIDS GALAXY TOUR'S &quot;HERO&quot; PLAYING]

609
00:37:48,016 --> 00:37:51,811
-Dance with me. -What's the point, Chuck?

610
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:53,271
We're never gonna be them.

611
00:37:56,024 --> 00:37:57,901
We said so, remember?

612
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:02,739
It's not for us.

613
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:04,574
Maybe.

614
00:38:04,783 --> 00:38:07,076
But I wouldn't change us.

615
00:38:07,744 --> 00:38:09,829
Not if it meant losing what we have.

616
00:38:10,663 --> 00:38:13,208
And what do we have, Chuck? You tell me.

617
00:38:15,335 --> 00:38:16,461
Tonight.

618
00:38:20,173 --> 00:38:25,512
So shut up and dance with me.

619
00:38:47,367 --> 00:38:49,452
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

620
00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:57,627
Hello?

621
00:38:57,836 --> 00:39:00,672
Yes. This is Lily Bass.

622
00:39:07,178 --> 00:39:09,973
Think maybe we should we wait for Aaron and Serena?

623
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:13,184
I thought it might be fun for the two of us to hang out.

624
00:39:13,393 --> 00:39:14,394
Alone.

625
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:15,687
Right. Right, alone.

626
00:39:15,895 --> 00:39:19,107
You know what? We came with them. I wouldn't wanna be rude.

627
00:39:19,315 --> 00:39:22,193
I don't know, are you hungry? Because I know a great place.

628
00:39:22,402 --> 00:39:24,529
-Dan. Hey. -Hey, guys, what's up?

629
00:39:24,737 --> 00:39:27,782
Do you mind if I talk to Dan for a second?

630
00:39:29,325 --> 00:39:32,662
No. No, I don't. I'm gonna-- I'll grab us a cab.

631
00:39:36,165 --> 00:39:37,834
I'll get one for us too.

632
00:39:39,502 --> 00:39:40,920
Mm.

633
00:39:42,839 --> 00:39:48,136
I just want to apologize for how I acted earlier.

634
00:39:48,344 --> 00:39:51,848
-I had no right. -No. No apology necessary.

635
00:39:53,182 --> 00:39:54,934
Good.

636
00:39:55,143 --> 00:39:57,145
Because I didn't want you to go tonight...

637
00:39:58,146 --> 00:40:05,111
...and do whatever it is you're gonna do without me just clearing the air first.

638
00:40:05,695 --> 00:40:07,739
Well, consider it cleared.

639
00:40:07,947 --> 00:40:09,657
And I didn't mean to pry earlier.

640
00:40:09,866 --> 00:40:11,868
No, I know.

641
00:40:15,204 --> 00:40:21,085
Well, good, we can both go with clean air.

642
00:40:22,462 --> 00:40:24,756
Yeah. Yeah, I guess so.

643
00:40:35,934 --> 00:40:39,812
Hey, it was meaningful with you.

644
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:43,650
It was the greatest night of my life.

645
00:40:46,027 --> 00:40:47,987
Mine too.

646
00:40:48,196 --> 00:40:52,075
Why does this feel like we're cutting some mythological tie?

647
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:55,119
I don't know, but it does.

648
00:40:55,328 --> 00:40:56,663
-Are we...? -Serena.

649
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:59,165
-Where's Charles? -I don't know.

650
00:40:59,374 --> 00:41:00,416
I need to find him.

651
00:41:00,625 --> 00:41:01,709
Mom, what's wrong?

652
00:41:04,420 --> 00:41:05,755
Bart's been in an accident.
